The  John Hancock Global
Opportunities  Fund outperformed other global equities mutual
funds in Bloomberg Rankingsâ€™ evaluation of long- and short-term
returns for the fifth straight time since June.  The John Hancock Advisers LLC investment pool, managed by
 Timothy Malloy ,  Roger Hamilton  and  Christopher Arbuthnot ,
returned 35.6 percent in the 12 months ended Nov. 12, an
annualized 9.5 percent over three years and 15 percent over five
years, Bloomberg data show.  The analysis evaluated five types of U.S., global and
emerging-market investments as well as commodities exchange-
traded funds as of Nov. 12. The previous ranking analyzed funds
as of Sept. 30.  A summary is below, with links to total-return data. For
the complete ranking, which evaluates U.S.-based funds based on
one-, three- and five-year total returns and an adjustment for
